[compilation snap-1][1] [compilation snap-2][2] I&#39;m trying to upgrade my project from java 1.8 to version 13.0.2. There were some unsupported functions which I removed. Unfortunately **toInstant()** is one of them.
My project uses it in a java module like this:

    Date date = format.parse(inputDate);
    finalDate = date.toInstant().toString();

Now I&#39;m not able to compile the code with toInstant() with JDK 13 because it says &#39;Symbol not found&#39; and compilation error occurs:

    [ERROR]   cannot find symbol
    [ERROR]   symbol:   method toInstant()
    [ERROR]   location: variable date of type java.util.Date
    [ERROR] -&gt; [Help 1]

So I looked out for several code replacements for toInstant() and decided to get rid of it by using few functions from java.time. But java.time is not found during compilation:

    package java.time does not exist

Does this denote that something is wrong with my JDK set up ? I&#39;m not facing any other issues apart from this one issue.
